	</style>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">IEEE.tv Offers New Features, Social Networking Options http://bit.ly/9GTfKm</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Survival Skills for Scientific Writing http://bit.ly/ct2Fgd</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Five Ways to Cut Your Junk Mail http://bit.ly/9INScp</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Diminutive, but not Disappeared: Rare dwarf lemur rediscovered 100 years after last sighting http://bit.ly/9lnBds</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Text Messages to Fight Fraud in Africa http://bit.ly/cY6YeJ</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Help Operation Teen Book Drop Deliver 10,000 Books  http://bit.ly/bMDBy0</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Losing the race: Illegal trade devastating Madagascar's radiated tortoise http://bit.ly/bu94Eg</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Navajo Nation's Irving Nelson Named Librarian of the Year  http://bit.ly/cKssva</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Be An Eco Hero, Win A Hawaiian Vacation from Sierra Club - http://bit.ly/cP82Ci</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">Facial recognition for penguins http://bit.ly/aSXkxm</p>  <p style="margin-bottom: 0in;">What's Your Paper Footprint? http://bit.ly/bqZjk8</p> <br /><br />Enjoy!

Man oh man, have I&nbsp;been busy the last week. In addition to the usual slate of articles and marketing projects, I have also been trying to concentrate on the creative work a bit more. I&nbsp;submitted 12 poems and 1 short story, received a rejection on another short story, and started work on my next mini-comics. (I&nbsp;have enough material written for two mini-comics, but finding time to draw them is another story.)<br /><br />I've also been dealing with deadly computer problems, as my old PC is just about ready to give up the ghost. Heck, it may have died yesterday. I'm waiting to hear back out from our trusty local IT&nbsp;guy before I&nbsp;take it into the woods and shoot it. (I'm working on my little netbook now, which is a decent little computer, if a bit slow. I have the big monitor and keyboard hooked up to it, so I&nbsp;can work without hunching over it like Quasimodo.)<br /><br />I&nbsp;have a new Dell on order, and it should have been here by now, but it was delayed until next week. I've read that all of the computer manufacturers are dealing with chip shortages caused by the financial slowdown, so let this be a triple lesson for you:&nbsp;1)&nbsp;If you're going to need a new computer, order it early. 2)&nbsp;Always have multiple backup systems in place. And 3)&nbsp;Always have a spare computer lying around for emergencies.<br /><br />Anyway, here's a list of most of my articles from the last week. A few of them were tied to specific dates, so they aren't timely any more. I'm sure you can still find them if you really want to read them.<br /><br />   	<div style="margin-left: 40px;"><meta http-equiv="CONTENT-TYPE" content="text/html; charset=utf-8"> 	<title></title> 	<meta name="GENERATOR" content="OpenOffice.org 2.4  (Linux)"> 	<style type="text/css">
